      • searchPathThreshhold

        public void searchPathThreshhold(java.lang.Float threshold,
                                 java.lang.String pathName)
        Execute a search function on the loaded graph with a threshold and a path as parameters. The search result may be lost if it is not stored immediately afterwards. Use saveLastSearchResult to do so.
        Parameters:
        threshold - the results with lower relatedness than the threshold will be ignored.
        pathName - the name of the path the search will be executed on.
        See Also:
        saveLastSearchResult()

        Execute a search function on the loaded graph with two nodes, a threshold and a path as parameters. The search result may be lost if it is not stored immediately afterwards. Use saveLastSearchResult to do so.
